iciliana; photo J. Prag 2023-05-09\" src=\"ISic003398_b-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>Provisional text from photographs\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2> translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">  \u003C/p>\u003Cp>  \u003C/p>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Two fragments (0.42x0.36m and 0.415 x 0.335m), large letters 15cm high in line 1, 10cm high in line 2. The fragments do not join, but are of the same inscription probably parts of an architectural element and probably part of a building inscription. Likely restoration of the name Pompeius in the first fragment, and to be linked to the statues from the same area.\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Libertini 1926 44 b \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001874\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001874\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003Cli> Patané 2011 47 and 154 fig. 36 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001682\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001682\u003C/a>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\"> Line 1-2  100-150  Interlineation line 1 to 2  80-90  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[216,219,222,225,228,231,234,237],{"id":217,"html":218},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"la\">  \u003Cspan class=\"textpartnumber\" id=\"aba\">fragment (physical) a\u003C/span>  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"la\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"diva--interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"aa-l1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan 